UNITED STATES of America, Appellant, v. Frank G. CARLSON, Appellee. No. 8381. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Nov. 16, 1936. John B. Tansil, U. S. Atty., and Francis J. McGan, Atty., Department of Justice, both of Butte, Mont. John W. Mahan, of Helena, Mont., for appellee.

Before WILBUR, GARRECHT, and DENMAN, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon stipulation of counsel for respective parties, ordered appeal dismissed, that a judgment of dismissal be filed and entered accordingly; mandate forthwith.
